cps (count per second) is a small linux program written in python that shows number of lines and bytes per second piped into the program.

Installation
------------
Copy "cps" to a PATH accessible directory (ex: /usr/local/bin/)

   sudo cp cps /usr/local/bin/ 
   sudo chmod a+x /usr/local/bin/cps

Example
--------
Line per second added to a log: tail -f log_file.log | cps

